# IBD Recipe Feature  
### Product Case Study

---

## Problem Statement

The non-profit organization wants to introduce a **Recipe** section on its website to support the IBD (Inflammatory Bowel Disease) community.
Currently, patients rely on external websites, blogs, and printed materials for dietary guidance. There is no centralized digital solution within the organizationâ€™s platform.
The goal is to provide structured, verified, and personalized recipe guidance directly through the website.

---

## Product Overview

**Product Name:** Recipe  

**Primary Objectives:**

- Centralize IBD-friendly recipes.
- Enable expert and community contributions.
- Improve patient engagement.
- Provide diet-based filtering and nutritional insights.

---

## Target Users

| User Type | Purpose |
|-----------|----------|
| Patient | Find recipes to manage symptoms |
| Caregiver | Search recipes for patients |
| Contributor | Submit verified recipes |
| Admin | Review and approve content |

---

## Current State (AS-IS)

- Patients redirected to external platforms.
- Printed materials not digitally accessible.
- No engagement tracking.
- No content moderation workflow.

---

## Future State (TO-BE)

1. User logs into platform.
2. Navigates to Recipe section.
3. Applies diet filters.
4. Views recipe with nutritional data.
5. Provides rating and feedback.
6. Contributor submits recipe.
7. Admin reviews and approves.

---

## Core Features

- Recipe submission form
- Role-based approval workflow
- Diet-based filtering
- Star ratings and feedback
- Nutritional calculator
- Admin dashboard

---

## Sample User Story

**User Story:**  
As a Patient, I want to filter recipes by diet type so that I can quickly find meals suitable for my condition.

**Acceptance Criteria:**

- Given the patient selects a diet filter  
- When the filter is applied  
- Then only matching recipes are displayed  

---

## MVP Scope

- Recipe submission
- Diet filtering
- Admin approval
- Feedback system
- Basic nutritional calculator

---

## Non-Functional Requirements

- Page load time under 3 seconds
- Role-based access control
- Secure data handling
- Scalable content management

---

## Success Metrics

- Monthly recipe submissions
- Approval rate
- Engagement rate (ratings, feedback)
- Repeat visits
- Reduction in external referrals

---

## Conclusion

The Recipe feature transforms the platform into a centralized dietary support ecosystem for IBD patients.
By combining structured submission workflows, role-based moderation, and personalized filtering, the solution ensures scalability, reliability, and community-driven engagement.

---


